Rating: 3
This was a nice flan, but was VERY sweet. This is even after omitting all caramel (I was out of it)! However, I added a touch more rum to make up for the loss of caramel flavor and that turned out nicely. The consistency was fine; this was served at room temperature. Took slightly longer to cook. Also, I threw in some pieces of coconut to provide a surprising chewiness to the flan and some extra flavor. That was very nice!

Rating: 4
Coconut lovers will delight in this creamy, smooth concotion bursting with intense coconut flavor. Do not omit the toasted coconut topping. I accidentally used 1/4. c caramel sauce for half the recipe. I needed to use 1/2 can of cream of coconut so omitted the sugar; the caramel and cream of coconut have plenty of sugar. The result was lip-smacking good. Any liqueur could be substituted for the rum. I used Triple Sec successfully. This will be my standard flan recipe. It's the best I've ever made.

